productName.name: productName
productName.description: The textual description of the IN3000.

productVersion.name: productVersion
productVersion.description: The version of the IN3000 Firmware.

releasedDate.name: releasedDate
releasedDate.description: The release date of this version.

compexPhone.name: compexPhone
compexPhone.description: Compex's phone number for technical support or sales information.

compexImage.name: compexImage
compexImage.description: Information on the system setup. This string is not in a human readable form.

compexMyAccess.name: compexMyAccess
compexMyAccess.description: This tells you the access you have with the community string you are using.

devTeamTable.name: devTeamTable
devTeamTable.description: This is a list of the Compex development team.

devTeamEntry.name: devTeamEntry
devTeamEntry.description: Information about a particular person. The index is the cpId of the person.

cpId.name: cpId
cpId.description: This is the development team member's unique identifier number.

cpName.name: cpName
cpName.description: This is the development team member's name.

communityTable.name: communityTable
communityTable.description: A table containing community string information.

communityEntry.name: communityEntry
communityEntry.description: Information about a particular community string. The instance of the table entries is the communityInstance.

communityInstance.name: communityInstance
communityInstance.description: The table instance. This is the row number of a particular community string in the table.

communityString.name: communityString
communityString.description: The community string. This is defined in RFC 1157. The community string may be up to 10 characters in length.

communityCapability.name: communityCapability
communityCapability.description: The capability of the community string. The community string may be valid for different SNMP operations. Setting this object to 'clear' will cause the entry to be cleared out.

trapTable.name: trapTable
trapTable.description: A table containing trap receiver information.

trapEntry.name: trapEntry
trapEntry.description: Information about a particular trap receiver. The instance for this table is the trapDest, or the IP address of the trap receiver. This table may have up to ten entries.

trapDest.name: trapDest
trapDest.description: The trap destination. This is defined in RFC 1157. The trap received should be the IP address of an SNMP based network management system.

trapStatus.name: trapStatus
trapStatus.description: The trap status. This MIB variable is used to delete a trap receiver from the trap table.

rptrFifoColls.name: rptrFifoColls
rptrFifoColls.description: The total number of Collision Designators put into the IN3000's FIFO.

rptrShortWoPort.name: rptrShortWoPort
rptrShortWoPort.description: The total number of short fragment put into the IN3000's FIFO without a port designator.

rptrNoStatsDsgntr.name: rptrNoStatsDsgntr
rptrNoStatsDsgntr.description: The total number of empty statistic designators put into the IN3000's FIFO.

rptrInvalidDesgntr.name: rptrInvalidDesgntr
rptrInvalidDesgntr.description: The total number of entries put into the IN3000's FIFO that had invalid designators.

rptrPortIDwoPacket.name: rptrPortIDwoPacket
rptrPortIDwoPacket.description: The total number of entries in the IN3000's FIFO which do not have a corresponding packet in the ethernet controller's RAM buffer.

rptrOverflows.name: rptrOverflows
rptrOverflows.description: The total number of times the IN3000's FIFO has overflowed.

rptrNoFreeBuffers.name: rptrNoFreeBuffers
rptrNoFreeBuffers.description: The number of packets received that had to be discarded due to lack of buffers.

rptrTxTimeouts.name: rptrTxTimeouts
rptrTxTimeouts.description: The total number of times a packet could not be sent before the transmit timer expired.

rptrNICTxCollisions.name: rptrNICTxCollisions
rptrNICTxCollisions.description: The total number of collision that occured while the ethernet controller attempted to transmit. This error is reported by the ethernet controller.

rptrNICTxFifoUruns.name: rptrNICTxFifoUruns
rptrNICTxFifoUruns.description: The total number of times the ethernet controller could not gain access to the ethernet before the ethernet controller's FIFO emptied.

rptrNICTxCDHrtbts.name: rptrNICTxCDHrtbts
rptrNICTxCDHrtbts.description: The number of times the ethernet controlled was unable to transmit a collision signal after transmission of a packet.

rptrNICTxOutWinCls.name: rptrNICTxOutWinCls
rptrNICTxOutWinCls.description: The total number of collisions seen by the ethernet controller that occured after the slot time.

rptrNICCarrierLost.name: rptrNICCarrierLost
rptrNICCarrierLost.description: The total number of times a carrier lost was detected by the ethernet controlled during the transmission of a packet.

rptrInNoRxBuf.name: rptrInNoRxBuf
rptrInNoRxBuf.description: The total number of times a packet was discarded due to lack of receive buffers.

groupOctetsTable.name: groupOctetsTable
groupOctetsTable.description: This table contains Repeater Group Level octets Statistics.

groupOctetsEntry.name: groupOctetsEntry
groupOctetsEntry.description: Each row of this table is associated to a TP3000 or RP3000. Note the the groups are numbered from 1 to 4.

gsoGroupIndex.name: gsoGroupIndex
gsoGroupIndex.description: A unique value to the group. The groups are numbered from 1 to 4. The addresses set via the dip switches on the TP3000 and RP3000 are numbered 0 to 3. In order to calculate the group number add one (1) to the address set via the TP3000 or RP3000 dip switches.

gsoHostOctetsRxOk.name: gsoHostOctetsRxOk
gsoHostOctetsRxOk.description: The total number of octets received by all ports in the group that were from valid packets and were addressed to the IN3000.

gsoHostOctetsRxErr.name: gsoHostOctetsRxErr
gsoHostOctetsRxErr.description: The total number of octets received by all ports in the group that were from packets with errors and were addressed to the IN3000.

gsoOctetsRxOk.name: gsoOctetsRxOk
gsoOctetsRxOk.description: The total number of octets received by all ports in the group that were from valid packets and were no addressed to the IN3000.

gsoOctetsRxErr.name: gsoOctetsRxErr
gsoOctetsRxErr.description: The total number of octets received by all ports in the group that were from packets with errors and were not addressed to the IN3000.

gsobkt64Ok.name: gsobkt64Ok
gsobkt64Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were 64 bytes in length (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt64Err.name: gsobkt64Err
gsobkt64Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were 64 bytes in length (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsobkt65to127Ok.name: gsobkt65to127Ok
gsobkt65to127Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 65 bytes and 127 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt65to127Err.name: gsobkt65to127Err
gsobkt65to127Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 65 bytes and 127 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsobkt128to255Ok.name: gsobkt128to255Ok
gsobkt128to255Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 128 bytes and 255 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt128to255Err.name: gsobkt128to255Err
gsobkt128to255Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 128 bytes and 255 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsobkt256to511Ok.name: gsobkt256to511Ok
gsobkt256to511Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 256 bytes and 511 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt256to511Err.name: gsobkt256to511Err
gsobkt256to511Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 256 bytes and 511 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsobkt512to1023Ok.name: gsobkt512to1023Ok
gsobkt512to1023Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 512 bytes and 1023 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt512to1023Err.name: gsobkt512to1023Err
gsobkt512to1023Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 512 bytes and 1023 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsobkt1024to1518Ok.name: gsobkt1024to1518Ok
gsobkt1024to1518Ok.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 1024 bytes and 1518 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

gsobkt1024to1518Err.name: gsobkt1024to1518Err
gsobkt1024to1518Err.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were between 1024 bytes and 1518 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

gsoRuntPacketsOk.name: gsoRuntPacketsOk
gsoRuntPacketsOk.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were less than 64 bytes, and did not contain any other errors.

gsoRuntPacketsErr.name: gsoRuntPacketsErr
gsoRuntPacketsErr.description: The total number of packets reveived from all ports in the group that were less than 64 bytes and contained errors.

gsoPacketsTooBigOk.name: gsoPacketsTooBigOk
gsoPacketsTooBigOk.description: The total number of packets reveived from all ports in the group that were larger than 1518 bytes, and did not contain any other errors.

gsoPacketsTooBigErr.name: gsoPacketsTooBigErr
gsoPacketsTooBigErr.description: The total number of packets reveived from all ports in the group that were larger than 1518 bytes, and contained other errors.

groupPacketTable.name: groupPacketTable
groupPacketTable.description: This table contains Repeater Group Level Packet Statistics.

groupPacketEntry.name: groupPacketEntry
groupPacketEntry.description: Each row of this table is associated to a TP3000 or RP3000. Note the the groups are numbered from 1 to 4.

gspGroupIndex.name: gspGroupIndex
gspGroupIndex.description: A unique value to the group. The groups are numbered from 1 to 4. The addresses set via the dip switches on the TP3000 and RP3000 are numbered 0 to 3. In order to calculate the group number add one (1) to the address set via the dip switches.

gspPacketsRxOk.name: gspPacketsRxOk
gspPacketsRxOk.description: The total number of packet received by all ports in the group that were valid packets.

gspPacketsRxErr.name: gspPacketsRxErr
gspPacketsRxErr.description: The total number of packet received by all ports in the group that were packets with errors.

gspPhysicalOk.name: gspPhysicalOk
gspPhysicalOk.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were unicast packets and were valid packets.

gspPhysicalErr.name: gspPhysicalErr
gspPhysicalErr.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were unicast packets and were packets with errors.

gspMulticastOk.name: gspMulticastOk
gspMulticastOk.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were multicast packets and were valid packets.

gspMulticastErr.name: gspMulticastErr
gspMulticastErr.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were multicast packets and were packets with errors.

gspBroadcastOk.name: gspBroadcastOk
gspBroadcastOk.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were broadcast packets and were valid packets.

gspBroadcastErr.name: gspBroadcastErr
gspBroadcastErr.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were broadcast packets and were packets with errors.

gspHostPhysicalOk.name: gspHostPhysicalOk
gspHostPhysicalOk.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were unicast packets, addressed to the IN3000 and did not have errors.

gspHostPhysicalErr.name: gspHostPhysicalErr
gspHostPhysicalErr.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that were unicast packets, addressed to the IN3000 and had errors.

groupMiscTable.name: groupMiscTable
groupMiscTable.description: This table contains Repeater Group Level Statistics.

groupMiscEntry.name: groupMiscEntry
groupMiscEntry.description: Each row of this table is associated to a TP3000 or RP3000. Note the the groups are numbered from 1 to 4.

gsmGroupIndex.name: gsmGroupIndex
gsmGroupIndex.description: A unique value to the group. The groups are numbered from 1 to 4. The addresses set via the dip switches on the TP3000 and RP3000 are numbered 0 to 3. In order to calculate the group number add one (1) to the address set via the dip switches.

gsmNumPorts.name: gsmNumPorts
gsmNumPorts.description: The total number of ports contained in the group.

gsmNumLinkUp.name: gsmNumLinkUp
gsmNumLinkUp.description: The total number of ports in the group that have link status.

gsmNumLinkPulses.name: gsmNumLinkPulses
gsmNumLinkPulses.description: The total number of ports in the group that have link pulses enabled.

gsmCollisions.name: gsmCollisions
gsmCollisions.description: The total number of collisions detected by all ports in the group.

gsmLateCollisions.name: gsmLateCollisions
gsmLateCollisions.description: The total number of late collisions detected by all ports in the group.

gsmPartitions.name: gsmPartitions
gsmPartitions.description: The total number of partitions from all ports in the group.

gsmJabbers.name: gsmJabbers
gsmJabbers.description: The total number of frames from all port in the group that were longer than 1518 bytes, and had a non integral number of bytes or a bad frame check sequence (FCS).

gsmShortFragments.name: gsmShortFragments
gsmShortFragments.description: Total number of packets from all ports in the group that were less than 64 bytes, and had a non-integral number of octets or had a bad frame check sequence (FCS).

gsmCrcFae.name: gsmCrcFae
gsmCrcFae.description: The total number of packets reveived from all ports in the group that had frame alignment errors. Since there was a frame alignment error the packet also had a bad CRC.

gsmCrc.name: gsmCrc
gsmCrc.description: The total number of packets received from all ports in the group that did not have a frame alignment error, but they had a bad CRC.

gsmFifoOverrun.name: gsmFifoOverrun
gsmFifoOverrun.description: The total number of packets reveived from all port in the group that caused the ethernet controlled to overrun its FIFO.

gsmDeferring.name: gsmDeferring
gsmDeferring.description: The total number of packets from all ports in the group that caused the ethernet controller to detect a jabber.

portOctetsTable.description: This table contains octet statistics that deal with the TP3000 and RP3000 ports.

portOctetsEntry.name: portOctetsEntry
portOctetsEntry.description: Each row in this table is associated with a port in a TP3000 or RP3000. Note that groups are numbered 1 to 4 and ports are numbered 1 to 7. The row instance is made up of the group number and the port number.

psoGroupIndex.name: psoGroupIndex
psoGroupIndex.description: The group that this port resides in. The groups are numbered 1 to 4.

psoPortIndex.name: psoPortIndex
psoPortIndex.description: The port number of this port. Note that the ports are numbered 1 to 7. For the TP3000 the twisted pair ports are numbered 1 to 6 and the remaining ethernet port (either 10base2 or AUI) is port 7.

psoHostOctetsRxOk.name: psoHostOctetsRxOk
psoHostOctetsRxOk.description: The total number of octets received on this port that were from packets without errors and were addressed to the IN3000.

psoHostOctetsRxErr.name: psoHostOctetsRxErr
psoHostOctetsRxErr.description: The total number of octets received on this port that were from packets with errors and were addressed to the IN3000.

psoOctetsRxOk.name: psoOctetsRxOk
psoOctetsRxOk.description: The total number of octets received on this port that were from packets without errors.

psoOctetsRxErr.name: psoOctetsRxErr
psoOctetsRxErr.description: The total number of octets received on this port that were from packets with errors.

psobkt64Ok.name: psobkt64Ok
psobkt64Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were 64 bytes in length (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt64Err.name: psobkt64Err
psobkt64Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were 64 bytes in length (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psobkt65to127Ok.name: psobkt65to127Ok
psobkt65to127Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 65 and 127 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt65to127Err.name: psobkt65to127Err
psobkt65to127Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 65 and 127 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psobkt128to255Ok.name: psobkt128to255Ok
psobkt128to255Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 128 and 255 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt128to255Err.name: psobkt128to255Err
psobkt128to255Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 128 and 255 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psobkt256to511Ok.name: psobkt256to511Ok
psobkt256to511Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 256 and 511 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt256to511Err.name: psobkt256to511Err
psobkt256to511Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 256 and 511 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psobkt512to1023Ok.name: psobkt512to1023Ok
psobkt512to1023Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 512 and 1023 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt512to1023Err.name: psobkt512to1023Err
psobkt512to1023Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 512 and 1023 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psobkt1024to1518Ok.name: psobkt1024to1518Ok
psobkt1024to1518Ok.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 1024 and 1518 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and did not contain errors.

psobkt1024to1518Err.name: psobkt1024to1518Err
psobkt1024to1518Err.description: The total number of packets receive by this port that were between 1024 and 1518 bytes in length inclusive (including FCS octets and excluding framing bits) and contained errors.

psoRuntPacketsOk.name: psoRuntPacketsOk
psoRuntPacketsOk.description: The total number of packets received by this port that were less than 64 bytes, but contained no other errors.

psoRuntPacketsErr.name: psoRuntPacketsErr
psoRuntPacketsErr.description: The total number of packets received by this port that were less than 64 bytes, and contained other errors.

psoPacketsTooBigOk.name: psoPacketsTooBigOk
psoPacketsTooBigOk.description: The total number of packets received by this port that were greater than 1518 bytes, but contained no other errors.

portPacketEntry.description: Each row in this table is associated with a port in a TP3000 or RP3000. Note that groups are numbered 1 to 4 and ports are numbered 1 to 7. The row instance is made up of the group number and the port number.

pspGroupIndex.name: pspGroupIndex
pspGroupIndex.description: The group that this port resides in. The groups are numbered 1 to 4.

pspPortIndex.name: pspPortIndex
pspPortIndex.description: The port number of this port. Note that the ports are numbered 1 to 7. For the TP3000 the twisted pair ports are numbered 1 to 6 and the remaining ethernet port (either 10base2 or AUI) is port 7.

pspPacketsRxOk.name: pspPacketsRxOk
pspPacketsRxOk.description: The total number of packets received on this port that did no have any errors.

pspPacketsRxErr.name: pspPacketsRxErr
pspPacketsRxErr.description: The total number of packets received on this port that had errors.

pspPhysicalOk.name: pspPhysicalOk
pspPhysicalOk.description: The total number of unicast packets received on this port that did not have any errors.

pspPhysicalErr.name: pspPhysicalErr
pspPhysicalErr.description: The total number of unicast packets received on this port that had errors.

pspMulticastOk.name: pspMulticastOk
pspMulticastOk.description: The total number of multicast packets received on this port that did no have any errors.

pspMulticastErr.name: pspMulticastErr
pspMulticastErr.description: The total number of multicast packets received on this port that have errors.

pspBroadcastOk.name: pspBroadcastOk
pspBroadcastOk.description: The total number of broadcast packets that were received by this port and had no errors.

pspBroadcastErr.name: pspBroadcastErr
pspBroadcastErr.description: The total number of broadcast packets that were received by this port and had errors.

pspHostPhysicalOk.name: pspHostPhysicalOk
pspHostPhysicalOk.description: The total number of unicast packets received by this port that were addressed to the IN3000 and had no errors.

pspHostPhysicalErr.name: pspHostPhysicalErr
pspHostPhysicalErr.description: The total number of unicast packets received by this port that were addressed to the IN3000 and had errors.

portMiscTable.name: portMiscTable
portMiscTable.description: This table contains statistics that deal with the TP3000 and RP3000 ports.

portMiscEntry.name: portMiscEntry
portMiscEntry.description: Each row in this table is associated with a port in a TP3000 or RP3000. Note that groups are numbered 1 to 4 and ports are numbered 1 to 7. The row instance is made up of the group number and the port number.

psmGroupIndex.name: psmGroupIndex
psmGroupIndex.description: The group that this port resides in. The groups are numbered 1 to 4.

psmPortIndex.name: psmPortIndex
psmPortIndex.description: The port number of this port. Note that the ports are numbered 1 to 7. For the TP3000 the twisted pair ports are numbered 1 to 6 and the remaining ethernet port (either 10base2 or AUI) is port 7.

psmName.name: psmName
psmName.description: The name assigned to this port.

psmLinkState.name: psmLinkState
psmLinkState.description: The link state of the port. Note that if link pulses are disabled then the link state will be up.

psmLinkPulses.name: psmLinkPulses
psmLinkPulses.description: This variable is used to check or set whether this port has link pulses enabled.

psmCollisions.name: psmCollisions
psmCollisions.description: The total number of collisions that were received by this port.

psmLateCollisions.name: psmLateCollisions
psmLateCollisions.description: The total number of late collisions that were received by this port.

psmPartitions.name: psmPartitions
psmPartitions.description: The total number of times this port entered the partitioned state.

psmJabbers.name: psmJabbers
psmJabbers.description: The total number of frames received by this port that were longer than 1518 bytes, and had a non- integral number of octets or had a bad frame check sequence (FCS).

psmShortFragments.name: psmShortFragments
psmShortFragments.description: The total number of frames received by this port that were less than 64 bytes, and had a non- integral number of octets or had a bad frame check sequence (FCS).

psmCrcFae.name: psmCrcFae
psmCrcFae.description: The total number of packets reveived by this port that had frame alignment errors. Since there was a frame alignment error the packet also had a bad CRC.

psmCrc.name: psmCrc
psmCrc.description: The total number of packets reveived by this port that did not have frame alignment errors but had a bad CRC.

psmFifoOverrun.name: psmFifoOverrun
psmFifoOverrun.description: The total number of packets reveived by this port that caused the ethernet controlled to overrun its FIFO.

psmDeferring.name: psmDeferring
psmDeferring.description: The total number of packets received by this port the caused the ethernet controller to detect a jabber.

initHeapSize.name: initHeapSize
initHeapSize.description: The initial heap memory size in bytes.

usedHeap.name: usedHeap
usedHeap.description: Amount of heap memory in use in bytes.

freeHeap.name: freeHeap
freeHeap.description: Amount of free heap memory in bytes.

heapStatus.name: heapStatus
heapStatus.description: The status of the heap. A notOk(2) response means the heap has been corrupted, and an ok(1) reponse means the heap is OK. The heap check is preformed at the time of memory coalescing and not on demand. Therefore, the value of the variable may not match the current state of the heap. If you wish to have the heap checked on demand please use the heapTest variable to preform this test.

mallocCalls.name: mallocCalls
mallocCalls.description: Number of times malloc() has been called.

reallocCalls.name: reallocCalls
reallocCalls.description: Number of times realloc() has been called.

callocCalls.name: callocCalls
callocCalls.description: Number of times calloc() has been called.

freeCalls.name: freeCalls
freeCalls.description: Number of times free() has been called.

noMemoryAvailable.name: noMemoryAvailable
noMemoryAvailable.description: The number of times that there was not enough memory to complete a memory allocation operation.

mnodeCoalesces.name: mnodeCoalesces
mnodeCoalesces.description: The number of times that the memory manager coalesced mnodes.

coalesceMemCalls.name: coalesceMemCalls
coalesceMemCalls.description: The number of times that the memory manager was called to coalesced mnodes.

coalesceThreshold.name: coalesceThreshold
coalesceThreshold.description: This variable is used to set the number of free calls before coalescing memory. This change takes effect as soon as the variable is changed.

inUnknownTypes.name: inUnknownTypes
inUnknownTypes.description: Number of ICMP packets received with unknown type fields.

bufferPoolEmpty.name: bufferPoolEmpty
bufferPoolEmpty.description: Number of times an ICMP packet was received and there were not enough available buffers.

dataBufferTooSmall.name: dataBufferTooSmall
dataBufferTooSmall.description: Number of times an ICMP packet was received and the data buffer was too small.

threadCreateReq.name: threadCreateReq
threadCreateReq.description: The number of thread create requests.

threadCreateOk.name: threadCreateOk
threadCreateOk.description: The number of successful thread creates.

threadCreateFail.name: threadCreateFail
threadCreateFail.description: The number of unsuccessful thread creates.

threadTableFull.name: threadTableFull
threadTableFull.description: The number of requests to create a thread that failed because the maximum number of threads were reached.

threadKill.name: threadKill
threadKill.description: The number of threads that have been killed.

threadMaximum.name: threadMaximum
threadMaximum.description: The maximum number of threads that may be created. The set will take effect the next time the IN3000 is initialized.

defaultStackSize.name: defaultStackSize
defaultStackSize.description: The default stack size (in bytes) for each thread. The set will take effect the next time the IN3000 is initialized.

defaultTimeSlice.name: defaultTimeSlice
defaultTimeSlice.description: The default time slice (in milliseconds) for each thread. The set will take effect the next time the IN3000 is initialized. All newly created threads will get the new time slice.

bogusInterrupts.name: bogusInterrupts
bogusInterrupts.description: The total number of bogus interrupts.

divideError.name: divideError
divideError.description: The total number of divide by zero error interrupts.

singleStep.name: singleStep
singleStep.description: The total number of single step interrupts.

breakpoint.name: breakpoint
breakpoint.description: The total number of break point interrupts.

interruptOverflow.name: interruptOverflow
interruptOverflow.description: The total number of interrupt overflows.

arrayBoundsCheck.name: arrayBoundsCheck
arrayBoundsCheck.description: The total number of array bound check interrupts.

invalidOpcode.name: invalidOpcode
invalidOpcode.description: Th total number of invalid op code interrupts.

escapeOpcode.name: escapeOpcode
escapeOpcode.description: The total number of escape opcode interrupts.
